    <stitle>ELECTRONIC ENGINE CONTROLS - CUMMINS CELECT - 1992 - 1993 - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0813502">
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>This chapter will:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Provide operation descriptions of International-installed components that work with the
                        Cummins CELECT engine controls.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Provide circuit diagrams and connector composites of the International electrical system.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Provide component locations.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Provide troubleshooting guides for International-installed components when the diagnostics
                        indicate that a problem may be present. These steps require the use of a Fluke 23 Digital
                        Multimeter (DMM).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The illustrations in Section 5.0 have been reproduced with permission of Cummins Engine
                        Company.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>To perform engine diagnostics, use the appropriate Cummins Troubleshooting and Repair Manual. Cummins
                publications can be ordered from local Cummins Distributors or:
            </para>
            <para>Cummins Engine Co.,Inc.</para>
            <para>Publishing Services CMC 40924</para>
            <para>Box 3005</para>
            <para>Columbus, IN 47202-3005</para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
            <title>1992 CUMMINS CELECT ELECTRONIC ENGINE CONTROLS</title>
            <para>CELECT is an electronically controlled, mechanically actuated unit injector diesel engine. The CELECT
                system provides an electronic fuel control system, electronic engine protection and other operational
                controls.
            </para>
            <para>CELECT is available on the L10 and N14 engines and controls the following functions:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Road speed governing</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Gear-down protection</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cruise control</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>PTO control</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Progressive shifting</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Idle shutdown</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Adjustable low idle speed (in-cab)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Choice of governor type (electronically selectable)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Self diagnostics</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine Protection System</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>Refer to the Cummins Engine Manual furnished with the vehicle for additional information.</para>
            <para>Since each CELECT control system is electronically programmable to individual owner specifications,
                <emph type="underscr">the operating parameters will vary from vehicle to vehicle</emph>. These
                parameters include: maximum cruise speed, shift schedules, governor type (automotive type or variable
                speed), idle RPM, full engine shutdown as part of the engine protection system and many others.
            </para>
            <para>The "Brain" of the CELECT system is the electronic control module (ECM) located on the left side of
                the engine. The ECM receives input from the following components:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Engine position sensor (EPS)*</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Vehicle speed sensor (VSS)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Throttle position sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Idle validation switch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Brake switch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Clutch switch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Boost pressure sensor*</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Coolant temperature sensor*</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Coolant level sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Ambient air pressure sensor*</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Intake manifold temperature sensor*</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Oil pressure sensor*</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Oil temperature sensor (behind ECM)*</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>*Cummins Sensors</para>
            <para>The ECM receives information from the sensors and switches and sends signals to the injectors, fuel
                shutoff valve, and engine brake relay.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
